"coach.action.next_time" = "Next step";
"coach.action.impact" = "What this changes";
"coach.abort.hungry.title" = "This looks more like an overly aggressive plan than a discipline problem";
"coach.abort.hungry.body" = "Stopping because you were too hungry usually means the current rhythm is a bit beyond your current state. Intermittent fasting works better when it is repeatable, not when one session is pushed to the limit.";
"coach.abort.hungry.detail" = "Use a steadier start time first, then consider making %@ a little gentler to improve completion.";
"coach.abort.social.title" = "One social interruption does not ruin your rhythm";
"coach.abort.social.body" = "Fasting should fit around life, not cut life in half. Getting interrupted by a meal out is more common and more normal than trying to compensate later.";
"coach.abort.social.detail" = "Return to your usual rhythm without compensating by extending the next session. If this happens often, give yourself a more flexible start window.";
"coach.abort.unwell.title" = "If you feel unwell, prioritize your physical state first";
"coach.abort.unwell.body" = "Intermittent fasting should be sustainable, not something you push through while feeling unwell. Stopping first is usually more important than forcing one session to the finish.";
"coach.abort.unwell.detail" = "Once you feel better, restart with a gentler plan. If discomfort keeps happening, do not extend duration yet.";
"coach.abort.other.title" = "A clear record is more useful than trying to make up for this session";
"coach.abort.other.body" = "One interruption does not erase the work before it. For intermittent fasting, honest records and regular review are usually more useful than compensating by chasing longer sessions.";
"coach.abort.other.detail" = "Restart on your normal rhythm tomorrow. Prioritize a stable start instead of immediately chasing a longer fast.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_start.title" = "Correcting the start time back to reality is a good habit";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_start.body" = "What matters more in a fast is how long the empty period really lasted. Setting the current session back to the actual start reflects your real rhythm better than leaving the record late.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_start.detail" = "The live timer, phase reminders, and weekly report will all recalculate from the new continuous duration.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_plan.title" = "The plan is corrected. Repeatability matters next";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_plan.body" = "Intermittent fasting is not about choosing the hardest plan. It is about choosing a rhythm you can repeat at a similar time of day. Once the plan is right, completion becomes meaningful.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_plan.detail" = "Run %@ steadily a few times before deciding whether to go longer.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_generic.title" = "The current session now matches your real rhythm";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_generic.body" = "Crossing midnight is not the key point. Recording the real session is. That keeps history, stats, and reminders aligned with what you actually did.";
"coach.ongoing.corrected_generic.detail" = "If you often open the app late, keep the true start time first and correct it afterward without splitting the session.";
"coach.ongoing.discarded.title" = "That accidental start has been removed cleanly";
"coach.ongoing.discarded.body" = "Accidental starts are common. Deleting the current session keeps history cleaner than leaving an aborted record that was never real.";
"coach.ongoing.discarded.detail" = "Keep history as a record of what really happened, not a log of taps. That makes later stats worth trusting.";
"coach.phase.tip_title" = "What matters more right now";
"coach.phase.early.title" = "This is a time-based phase cue, not a diagnosis";
"coach.phase.early.body" = "FastFlow phases are educational cues based on how long you have already been fasting. They help explain the general rhythm you are in. Real physiological responses do not happen at the exact same hour for everyone.";
"coach.phase.early.tip" = "Early on, recording the true start time matters more than pushing longer. Once the start time is accurate, later phases, reminders, and reports become more trustworthy.";
"coach.phase.middle.title" = "Phase changes are progress cues, not precise confirmation of body state";
"coach.phase.middle.body" = "In the middle phase, the app uses time to show your rhythm is progressing. This is still time-driven guidance and not a medical confirmation that you have entered a precise metabolic state.";
"coach.phase.middle.tip" = "If today started later than usual, correct the session back to the real start. For intermittent fasting, continuous duration and consistency matter more than whether the session crossed midnight.";
"coach.phase.late.title" = "A longer fasting phase is still guidance, not a diagnosis";
"coach.phase.late.body" = "At longer durations, FastFlow highlights that you have maintained an extended fasting rhythm. These phase notes explain progress and routine. They do not make medical claims about body state.";
"coach.phase.late.tip" = "At longer durations, keep the focus on sustainability and repeatability. A rhythm you can repeat matters more than a one-off long session.";
"coach.weekly.keep.step1" = "Keep the same start-time window and try to land 4 to 5 days in a similar range.";
"coach.weekly.keep.step2" = "Do not rush to extend duration yet. Let the current rhythm stay steady for another week.";
"coach.weekly.keep.step3" = "If dinner keeps moving later, pull your eating finish time a little earlier first.";
"coach.weekly.stabilize.step1" = "Pick the start time you can repeat most easily and pin the reminder there.";
"coach.weekly.stabilize.step2" = "Next week, prioritize a steadier start time instead of chasing longer durations at the same time.";
"coach.weekly.stabilize.step3" = "Even an occasionally shorter fast is better than large daily drift in start time.";
"coach.weekly.improve.step1" = "Keep the current plan and try to complete the goal one more day next week.";
"coach.weekly.improve.step2" = "If one day misses the goal, do not compensate by stretching the next session.";
"coach.weekly.improve.step3" = "Protect the start rhythm first, then improve completion.";
"coach.weekly.gentler.step1" = "Make the plan slightly gentler next week to trade for a better completion rate.";
"coach.weekly.gentler.step2" = "The goal is not a perfect session. It is 3 to 4 real completed sessions.";
"coach.weekly.gentler.step3" = "If hunger keeps interrupting the fast, lighten the plan before blaming yourself.";
"coach.weekly.build.step1" = "Aim to log 3 real sessions first, even if they are not very long.";
"coach.weekly.build.step2" = "Give yourself one fixed start window so getting started feels easier.";
"coach.weekly.build.step3" = "This week is about starting, not maxing out a single session.";
"coach.weekly.headline.keep" = "Protect the rhythm you have already stabilized";
"coach.weekly.headline.stabilize" = "Fix start-time drift next week first";
"coach.weekly.headline.improve" = "The focus next week is one more completed day";
"coach.weekly.headline.gentler" = "Move the plan to something easier to complete";
"coach.weekly.headline.build" = "Get the first real set of records in place";
"coach.action.plan.title" = "Set the default plan to %@";
"coach.action.plan.detail" = "Switch to an easier rhythm first, then build confidence through repeated completion.";
"coach.action.reminder.title" = "Set the start reminder to %@";
"coach.action.reminder.detail" = "Pinning the reminder to a steadier start time is usually easier to sustain than pushing on the fly.";
"education.guardrail.phase.title" = "Phase content should stay educational and supportive";
"education.guardrail.phase.guidance" = "Phase copy should be framed as time-based guidance and should not imply the app is diagnosing a medically confirmed body state.";
"education.guardrail.session.title" = "The fasting session is the primary truth";
"education.guardrail.session.guidance" = "A fast should always be saved as one complete session from startAt to endAt. Daily reporting is only a view layer and should not redefine the fast itself.";
"education.guardrail.midnight.title" = "Midnight is not a physiological reset point";
"education.guardrail.midnight.guidance" = "When explaining overnight fasts, emphasize duration, timing, and regularity instead of treating 00:00 as a boundary where the body resets.";
"education.duration.title" = "Continuous fasting duration is the base unit";
"education.duration.summary" = "A fasting session is defined first by how long it lasts, not by whether it crosses a calendar day.";
"education.duration.body" = "For most intermittent fasting users, one fast is best understood as a continuous fasting session. From 8:00 PM last night to 12:00 PM today is still one continuous 16-hour fast. Crossing midnight does not reset it.";
"education.duration.product1" = "Plan and timer surfaces should emphasize fasting duration before date boundaries.";
"education.duration.product2" = "History and stats should save the full session first, then decide how to display it by day.";
"education.duration.product3" = "Copy for overnight fasts should emphasize continuous duration to reduce confusion about date ownership.";
"education.duration.analytics1" = "Each fasting record should use the full session as the source of truth.";
"education.duration.analytics2" = "Daily charts may split duration by date, but streaks and completion should not be inferred from daily total duration alone.";
"education.duration.ref1" = "The study defines time-restricted feeding as a continuous eating window and fasting window rather than something that resets at midnight.";
"education.duration.ref2" = "The paper defines TRF as a longer daily fasting period, supporting duration rather than calendar boundaries as the core unit.";
"education.timing.title" = "Time of day affects the fasting experience";
"education.timing.summary" = "The same 16-hour fast usually aligns better with circadian rhythm when eating ends earlier rather than later.";
"education.timing.body" = "Research tends to support earlier daytime eating windows and avoiding regular late-night eating. Duration matters in intermittent fasting, but when you eat also matters.";
"education.timing.product1" = "Future plan suggestions can gently encourage ending the eating window earlier.";
"education.timing.product2" = "Notification copy should encourage daytime regularity rather than just pushing longer durations.";
"education.timing.product3" = "Phase explanations can add gentle reminders about aligning with daily routine.";
"education.timing.analytics1" = "Later advanced analysis can track the start and end of the eating window.";
"education.timing.analytics2" = "Weekly reports can surface insights such as consistently late eating finish times.";
"education.timing.ref1" = "This study tested early time-restricted feeding and reported improvements in some cardiometabolic markers.";
"education.timing.ref2" = "The paper notes that early TRF aligns with circadian rhythms in metabolism better than later schedules.";
"education.consistency.title" = "Consistency usually matters more than the occasional perfect session";
"education.consistency.summary" = "Intermittent fasting works better as a long-term rhythm than a pattern of large daily swings.";
"education.consistency.body" = "If daily eating and fasting rhythm varies too much, it becomes harder for both the body and the habit to stabilize. For most people, a sustainable and repeatable rhythm matters more than the occasional ideal session.";
"education.consistency.product1" = "FastFlow should emphasize easier long-term consistency rather than harder and longer fasting.";
"education.consistency.product2" = "Notifications and weekly reports can reinforce rhythm through stable start times, end times, and completed days.";
"education.consistency.product3" = "Streaks and consistency scores fit our product better than a single longest session.";
"education.consistency.analytics1" = "Later we can add schedule consistency metrics such as start-time drift over the last 7 days.";
"education.consistency.analytics2" = "Charts should not reward longest duration alone. They should also reflect rhythm stability.";
"education.consistency.ref1" = "The AHA summary notes that irregular patterns of total caloric intake are generally unfavorable for weight maintenance and cardiovascular health.";
"education.session.title" = "Date is a reporting unit, not the fast itself";
"education.session.summary" = "The body does not reset at 00:00, but product reporting still needs dates.";
"education.session.body" = "Overnight fasts are common. Physiologically, what matters is how long you stayed in a continuous fast and whether your eating times are regular. For records, date is only there for calendar views, weekly trends, and completion reporting.";
"education.session.product1" = "The product should treat the full session as truth, then split duration across dates for charts.";
"education.session.product2" = "Today's completion, streaks, and total fasting duration should use different attribution rules.";
"education.session.product3" = "Overnight fast copy should help users understand the distinction: physiology is continuous, reports are split by day.";
"education.session.analytics1" = "DailySummary works better as a day-level aggregation cache than as the only source of truth.";
"education.session.analytics2" = "The model needs both daily duration attribution and session completion attribution.";
"education.session.ref1" = "This is a product design inference based on fasting-session continuity and meal-timing research, not a direct quote from one single paper.";
